    "body": "The first commit in this PR adds a `btck_chainstate_manager_set_clock_time` API which lets kernel applications run validation code in a more deterministic way which does not depend on the system clock. This is an alternative to #35496, and one of several alternatives discussed in that PR with some tradeoffs described in https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/35496#issuecomment-4735710317.\r\n\r\nThe second commit changes the time library to prevent unintentional access to `NodeClock::now`, `SteadyClock::now`, and `GetTime` functions from kernel code by triggering link errors if they are called. The commit could be dropped from this PR, and I mostly wrote it as a way to be sure there the first commit was complete and all call sites were using the right clock times. The commit is also potentially useful because it removes `GetTime` calls from kernel code. `GetTime` calls have been deprecated the since introduction of `NodeClock` in #25101 and should be replaced by `NodeClock` calls.",
